### Changelog — All Releases

---

#### v0.2.0 — July 7, 2026

**Backend Security Hardening**
- httpOnly cookie session auth — access token + 7-day refresh token; refresh token rotated on every use; mobile UA detection sends tokens in response body too
- Atomic Lua sliding-window rate limiter (TOCTOU race closed)
- PostgreSQL RLS now load-bearing: migration 000057 creates `xcloak_app` DML-only role; app pool connects as `xcloak_app`; superuser bypassing RLS is closed
- Kafka event bus wired: 5 publish functions called; 6 consumer groups processing events
- FIM violations on critical paths auto-create `quarantine_file` tasks (pending approval)
- YARA matches auto-create `quarantine_file` tasks (pending approval)
- High-risk audit events streamed to Splunk HEC in real time (13 action codes)
- Splunk config cached in-process (2-min TTL) — removes per-event DB round-trip
- Webhook retry: immediate → 5 s → 30 s for all integrations (Slack, PD, Teams, Jira, ServiceNow, Splunk, generic)
- `xcloak_webhook_deliveries_total` Prometheus counter (by integration + outcome)
- `APP_BASE_URL` env var — replaces hardcoded localhost in password-reset/invite emails
- `logRecover()` replaces all silent `recover()` calls — panics visible in structured logs
- Zero `fmt.Printf`/`fmt.Println` in backend — full structured slog throughout
- Audit logging added for `LOG_RETENTION_CHANGE` and `SECURITY_POLICY_UPDATE`

**Go Agent — Enterprise Upgrade**
- `log/slog` throughout — `LOG_FORMAT=json` / `LOG_LEVEL` env controls
- Connections enriched with PID, process name, process path (`/proc/net` inode→PID on Linux; netstat+tasklist on Windows)
- User inventory: groups, sudo access, SSH key presence, last login, account locked status, home dir, GID
- Package collection: full fallback chain (dpkg→rpm→pacman→snap→flatpak→pip3 simultaneously on Linux; WMIC→registry→winget on Windows); `source` field added
- FIM: mode, UID, GID, mtime per file via `syscall.Stat_t`; extended watch paths
- New collectors: cron jobs, kernel modules (lsmod/driverquery), SUID/SGID binary scan, disk usage
- Heartbeat: load_avg_1m/5m/15m, logged_in_users, open_fds (Linux); cpu_load_pct, logged_in_users (Windows)
- 4 new server-dispatched task types

**Mobile Agent — Enterprise Upgrade**
- `DevicePosture` expanded: 8 → 24 fields (battery, storage, RAM, VPN, USB debug, unknown sources, security patch, manufacturer, SDK, fingerprint)
- `PostureCollector` rewrite: battery via `dumpsys battery`, storage via `df /data`, RAM from `/proc/meminfo`, VPN via interface list, Magisk socket check
- `EnrollmentService` sends full posture snapshot + build fingerprint at enrollment
- `ApiClient` retry: exponential backoff ×3 (500ms→1s→2s+jitter) for 5xx/429/SocketException/Timeout; 30s timeout
- 5 background timers with ≤30s jitter: check-in (5m), cmd poll (2m), log forward (10m), app inventory (30m), threat scan (15m)
- New MDM commands: `collect_posture`, `scan_threats`, `rotate_token`, `update_agent`
- `LogForwarder`: 11 security-relevant logcat tags; severity field per line; 200-line batches
- Consecutive failure tracking → foreground notification degrades to "Agent degraded" after 5 failures
- Pending message delivery: `message` command stores text; shown as AlertDialog on next app open
- Posture tab: 10 checks, Hardware sub-score, Device Status card with battery/storage progress bars

**Project Polish**
- `SECURITY.md` with threat model, audit status, responsible disclosure
- `CONTRIBUTING.md` with dev setup, code guidelines, PR process
- `CHANGELOG.md` and `roadmap.md`
- GitHub issue templates (bug report, feature request)
- GitHub Actions: build CI (Go+Flutter+Helm), Docker push, release workflow (binaries + APK + Helm chart)
- Helm chart bumped to v0.2.0

